<subSubSection pageId="56" pageNumber="814" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="56.[790,1382,1697,2125]" pageId="56" pageNumber="814">
<taxonomicName box="[791,1053,1776,1809]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="814" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wmbricatus">Hypsugo wmbricatus</taxonomicName>
has been considered conspecific with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1034,1186,1815,1848]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="814" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotis">H. macrotis</taxonomicName>
, but they are generally recognized as distinct species, based on morphological data; the relationship of this species to other congeners is still unclear. Specimens attributed to this species from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1104,1262,2012,2045]" name="Philippines" pageId="56" pageNumber="814">Philippines</collectingCountry>
actually represent 
<taxonomicName box="[934,1207,2052,2085]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="814" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="javanicus">Pipistrellus javanicus</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
